aste my time”</li>\r\n	<li>“I don’t want to worry about setting up my own servers”</li>\r\n	<li>“I want to see how the campaigns (and my agents) perform right now”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSo why does technology often become more complicated than it needs to/should be?\r\n\r\n1. Vendors work too hard to make one solution fit everyone\r\n\r\n2. Product development is often driven by engineers (no offense, guys) or small product teams in isolation, rather than involving actual users\r\n\r\n3. Every update of every product is “expected” to have some new (and cool) features, while all the old stuff is still there (kind of like your sock drawer – you need to throw away some of the old ones to make room for the new ones).\r\n\r\nThe Wired article also features a quote by Mike Monteiro, author of “Design Is a Job” which we believe helps explain what is happening: “We live in a culture of consumption, where quality is associated with more. So designers and manufacturers tend to believe that to succeed you have to provide more. What if Microsoft announced that the next version of Office had 75% less functionality? It would be usable! But there is no way marketing would let them get away with that.”\r\n\r\nApple created the iPhone and blew all competition away due to its unique design and the simplicity compared to the (all of sudden) clunky phones at the time. Likewise Google created a search experience that was so much better than everyone else due to its…SIMPLICITY. So here we are. BlueCloud is all about bringing simplicity to the call centres. Contact us to find out how you can become king in your own castle. Time to get in the driver’s seat folks. Find out how good it feels to be in control with all the power of the latest cloud technology under the hood.','Simplicity in call centre applications','','inherit','closed','open','','1440-revision-4','','','2013-06-19 09:29:08','2013-06-18 23:29:08','',1440,'http://localhost:8080/restorewp/1440-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1451,5,'2013-06-19 09:32:02','2013-06-18 23:32:02','<h1></h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<em id=\"__mceDel\"><em><a title=\"Wikipedia\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Predictive_dialer\" target=\"_blank\">Wikipedia:</a> A predictive dialer dials a list of telephone numbers and connects answered dials to people making calls, often referred to as agents. Predictive dialers use statistical algorithms to minimize the time that agents spend waiting between conversations, while minimizing the occurrence of someone answering when no agent is available.</em></em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA lot of people are using a predictive dialer / predictive dialler as an important tool to increase productivity in their outbound sales process, but we are often talking to companies that have not yet used such technology. They cite a few key reasons why:\r\n<strong>\r\nToo expensive\r\n</strong>Purchasing a stand alone predictive dialer can cost anywhere from $30,000 to $200,000 (excluding cost of maintenance and service agreements) and this of often too high to consider for smaller telemarketing companies or sales teams, as this may not even be feasible with their current cash flow (even if the ROI of the dialer may be only 12 months).<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Clunky</strong>\r\nMany people find dialers very complicated to use and get frustrated with the amount of time required to configure even a small campaign. Even after all this configuration they may not be able to make simple changes to the campaign or get reporting on the metrics they need.  <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Requires Expertise</strong>\r\nAcquiring a dialer also means that someone needs to know how to use it. Ideally there should be a few people who know this, even in small to mid-sized organisations. In addition to training cost, this normally also means increasing the headcount and added cost for the company.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nBut wait…this article was supposed to talk about the benefits of predictive dialers, not about the barriers. The reality is that many companies can still justify the cost and the additional headcount due to the huge increases in productivity. BlueCloud is now here to take this even further.\r\n\r\nAs we have already demonstrated to a lot of small and mid-sized teams, our technology provides a way to get all benefits of a predictive dialler WITHOUT any of the problems/barriers mentioned above. How?<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Cost</strong>\r\nFirst of all, there is no capital spent up front, and just a small subscription fee paid each month. The subscription fee has no contracts, and BlueCloud therefore remains flexible to your changing needs. Pay only for what you use.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Simplicity</strong>\r\nWe have removed the complexity of using this type of tools and have made it possible for anyone with enough skills configure their Facebook profile to use BlueCloud comfortably.\r\n\r\n<strong>No hardware</strong>\r\nNo specialists required. All you need is an internet connected computer with a headset for your agents. You don’t even need desktop phones!<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAnd now, finally, the big question: What are these 3 key benefits of a predictive dialer?\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>1. Increase number of connected calls</strong></span>\r\nIt is common to increase the number of connected calls in a day by more than 70%. No more time wasted waiting for unconnected calls and answering machines (yes we automatically detect this with BlueCloud). That is one massive jump in productivity!<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>2. Get in charge of your metrics</strong></span>\r\nAgain, a good dialer will give you access to all key campaign metrics whenever you need them. How many calls have been made, how many connected, how many per outcome (e.g. how many sales), etc. Best of all, you can get this per agent or per team or filter the results according to your requirements. This is how to keep the client happy and also how to keep making your team better.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>3. Get control over callbacks</strong></span>\r\nA good dialer (not all) will give you a full overview over callbacks agreed by the agents, nicely sorted by date and time.\r\n\r\nGood luck and don’t forget to ask your technology provider some tough questions. Can at least say that we are ready to answer.\r\n\r\n</div>','Top 3 benefits of a predictive dialler (dialer)','','inherit','closed','open','','1432-revision-4','','','2013-06-19 09:32:02','2013-06-18 23:32:02','',1432,'http://localhost:8080/restorewp/1432-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1452,5,'2013-06-19 09:08:10','2013-06-18 23:08:10','If you are new to Cloud Computing, this video by Macquarie Telecom brings you the basics if you have 4 minutes and 52 seconds to spare. Recommended.\r\n\r\n[video type=\"youtube\" id=\"whkyRvugqlM\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Introduction to Cloud Computing','','inherit','closed','open','','1427-revision-4','','','2013-06-19 09:08:10','2013-06-18 23:08:10','',1427,'http://localhost:8080/restorewp/1427-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1453,5,'2013-06-19 09:35:37','2013-06-18 23:35:37','If you are new to Cloud Computing, this video by Macquarie Telecom brings you the basics if you have 4 minutes and 52 seconds to spare. Recommended.\r\n\r\n[video type=\"youtube\" id=\"whkyRvugqlM\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Introduction to Cloud Computing','','inherit','closed','open','','1427-revision-5','','','2013-06-19 09:35:37','2013-06-18 23:35:37','',1427,'http://localhost:8080/restorewp/1427-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1454,5,'2013-06-19 09:35:37','2013-06-18 23:35:37','<span style=\"color: #333399;\">“Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication”</span>\r\n\r\n- LEONARDO DA VINCI\r\n\r\n[responsive]<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/restorewp/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Microwave.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1441\" 