 arrangement for the staff, but for you as an operator this means you can scale up and down much more in line with your changing needs. While some staff may still be employed in a full time basis, you could also have a whole \"army\" of freelancers you could call in when required.\n\nThe above mentioned cost savings will also give you far less flexibility to move with the market opportunities in terms of the types of work you and your team are doing.\n\n<strong>3. Increased Productivity</strong>\n\nHappy agents will increase your productivity significantly. They will no longer be stuck in traffic or because their spouse forgot to pick the kids up from school. This productivity boost will be visible on your bottom line at the end of each month.\n\n<strong>4. Higher staff satisfaction</strong>\n\nSer\n\n&nbsp;','4 reasons why you should consider home based agents','','inherit','closed','open','','1480-revision','','','2013-06-20 12:38:14','2013-06-20 02:38:14','',1480,'http://localhost:8080/restorewp/1480-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1483,5,'2013-06-20 12:46:45','2013-06-20 02:46:45','It has never been easier to employ home based agents for your team or even running a virtual call centre where all agents are working from home. Technology is the key enabler here, as cloud solutions are becoming more mainstream. There is now full transparency of all calls made, calls can be recorded and reports are easily available for management. BlueCloud is designed to work seamlessly with home based staff, and would give you an opportunity to have agents accessing the system from anywhere.\n\nA number of studies have shown that productivity and reductions in staff turnover often follow when staff are given options to work from home, but I won\'t bore you with statistics on this. However, there keep the 4 reasons in mind of you are considering this for your organisation:\n\n<strong>1. Cost savings</strong>\n\nDepending on how you manage your home based team there are a few obvious 